    <text corresp="#W240">
        <body>
            <div>
                <head><handShift new="#H_anonymous"/>O NOSSO INQUERITO SOBRE O FADO</head>
                <argument rend="center">
                    <p>O FADO SERÁ OU NÃO UMA CANÇÃO NACIONAL? – OS SEUS INTUITOS SÃO MORALISADORES,
                        OU PELO CONTRARIO ANTINGIRÃO UMA FEIÇÃO DISSOLVENTE? – HA VANTAGEM EM DAR AO
                        FADO O DESENVOLVIMENTO NECESSARIO A ELEGE-LO COMO UMA ESPECIALISAÇÃO
                        ARTISTICA, ETNICA, OU MUSICAL? – TURISTICO, POETICO, SAUDOSISTA, INVOCATIVO,
                        REGIONAL, REPRESENTA O FADO UMA EXPRESSÃO DE BELEZA, DE PROPAGANDA, DE
                        ATRAÇÃO NACIONAL?</p>
                    <p>TEEM A PALAVRA, ESCRIPTORES E ARTISTAS:</p>
                </argument>
                <!-- JU: Should we mark in the TEI that this introduction was not written by Pessoa?
                U: there is an attribute @hand which could be used to mark passages not written by Pessoa.
                As value, it takes a pointer to a person identified elswhere, e.g. 
                <argument hand="#Anonymous">
                Do you think you will need this more often and that it is important to mark it in the TEI?
                Then we could add this attribute and some necessary elements related to it in the TEI header.
                Otherwise or also in addition, maybe it would be an option to describe such cases in the general 
                note in the TEI header.
                JU: I'm not sure I'm seing all the implications this has, we will have some text that 
                have introductions not by Pessoa, I think in most cases we will not know who the 
                author is.I Think it can be important to mark them as diferent kind of texts in the edition, 
                if you think argument is the tool I think we should use it
                
                U: Ok, we can take this file as an example, I'll add what's necessary and put comments to it.
                It was a misunderstanding about <argument>: that element is only for the introduction here (because 
                it is an introductary part after the heading about what is going to follow). The different 
                responsibilities of authorship are only encoded in the attribute @hand.
                This attribute can be added to elements saying that this was written by another "hand". The value
                of the attribute is a pointer to a note on the hand in the TEI header (see above).
                I tried to add this to <head>s and <argument> above, but it is not allowed on <argument> by the TEI.
                (I will try to request a change in the TEI Guidelines for that because I don't understand why it 
                should not be allowed there). However, we need a working solution in the meanwhile. Another option
                is to use <handShift> to say where the author changes. This is introduced as an empty 
                element (it does not have any content itself and is closed right away: <handShift/>) at the points
                where something changes. Following the TEI schema, it needs to be put inside of <head>, <p>, or similar,
                directly in <div> is not possible. (I don't know why)
                I am not very sure about these solutions, I will do some consultation.
                
                Another question is if these shifts should be marked in the HTML somehow or not at all.
                JU: I think in the HTML we don't need any marks. I'll wait to see what you think is best for the formulation. 
                I eliminated the extra head, because that last line is part of the argument
                
                -->
                <p rend="indent-first"><handShift new="#H_FP"/>Toda a poesia – e a canção é uma
                    poesia ajudada – reflete o que a alma não tem. Porisso a canção dos povos
                    tristes é alegre, e a canção dos povos alegres é triste.</p>
                <p rend="indent-first">O fado, porém, não é alegre nem triste. É um episodio de
                    intervalo. Formou-o a alma portuguesa quando não existia e desejava tudo sem ter
                    força para o desejar.</p>
                <p rend="indent-first">As almas fortes atribuem tudo ao Destino; só os fracos
                    confiam na vontade propria, porque ela não existe.</p>
                <p rend="indent-first">O fado é o cansaço da alma forte, o olhar de desprezo de
                    Portugal ao Deus em que creu e tambem o abandonou.</p>
                <p rend="indent-first">No fado os Deuses regressam legitimos e longinquos. É, êsse o
                    segundo sentido da figura de El-Rei D. <rs type="name" key="P21" style="b"
                        >Sebastião</rs>.</p>
                <signed rend="right">Fernando Pessoa</signed>
            </div>
